{"id": "27838", "post": "<div class=\"post-27838 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-tutorials tag-billing-software tag-piracy tag-software tag-whmcs\" id=\"post-27838\"><h2 class=\"storytitle\"><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/how-to-verify-whmcs-licenses/\" rel=\"bookmark\">How to Verify WHMCS Licenses</a></h2><div class=\"meta\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" data-src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" alt=\"Tags: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/billing-software/\" rel=\"tag\">billing software</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/piracy/\" rel=\"tag\">piracy</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/software/\" rel=\"tag\">Software</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/whmcs/\" rel=\"tag\">WHMCS</a> <img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" alt=\"Date/Time: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> July 26, 2021 @ 12:00 am, by raindog308</div><div class=\"storycontent tablelook\"><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/whmcs_logo.png.webp\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-26670 litespeed-loaded\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/whmcs_logo.png.webp\" alt=\"WHMCS Logo\" width=\"400\" height=\"139\" align=\"right\" hspace=\"20\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/whmcs_logo.png.webp 400w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/whmcs_logo-300x104.png.webp 300w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px\" sizes=\"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px\" srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/whmcs_logo.png.webp 400w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/whmcs_logo-300x104.png.webp 300w\" data-was-processed=\"true\"><br>\nWhen new provider submit offers, one of the many checks we perform is to see if their WHMCS license is valid (assuming they\u2019re using WHMCS of course). Generally about once a month we get an offer from a provider who is using a cracked or nulled WHMCS installation.&nbsp; While the WHMCS setup looks normal if you\u2019re browsing it on their web site, there is an easy tool that WHMCS provides to validate licenses.</p><p>Regardless of the <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/meme-monday-were-oakley-capital-and-were-here-to-help/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" aria-label=\"Oakley Capital Meme\">community\u2019s feelings towards WHMCS</a> and their business model, we do not condone using pirated versions of their software.&nbsp;&nbsp;For as long as I\u2019ve been reading LowEndTalk, the <a href=\"https://www.lowendtalk.com/discussion/153228/rules-for-selling-on-lowendtalk-updated-may-2021/p1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">rules</a> have stated:</p><p><em>\u201cUsing a nulled WHMCS (or other nulled billing software) grants you and your company a lifetime ban on LET.\u201d</em></p><p>The same rule applies to LowEndBox.</p><p>Here\u2019s how to verify if someone\u2019s WHMCS is valid.</p><p><span id=\"more-27838\"></span></p><p>1. Visit the WHMCS license verification tool: <a href=\"https://www.whmcs.com/members/verifydomain.php\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" aria-label=\"WHMCS License Verify\">https://www.whmcs.com/members/verifydomain.php</a></p><p>2. Enter the domain in question.&nbsp; Note that only the top part of the domain should be entered \u2013 e.g., examplehost.com, not billing.examplehost.com.</p><p>3. Click Submit and you\u2019ll get either one of two reports.&nbsp; If the domain is valid:</p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/whmcs-lic-ver-2.png\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-27840 litespeed-loaded\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/whmcs-lic-ver-2.png\" alt=\"WHMCS License Verification\" width=\"600\" height=\"359\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/whmcs-lic-ver-2.png 600w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/whmcs-lic-ver-2-300x180.png 300w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/whmcs-lic-ver-2.png 600w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/whmcs-lic-ver-2-300x180.png 300w\" data-was-processed=\"true\"></p><p>Or if not, a screen that looks like this:</p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI2MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMzY2IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNjAwIDM2NiI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-27839\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/whmcs-lic-ver-1.png\" alt=\"WHMCS License Verification\" width=\"600\" height=\"366\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/whmcs-lic-ver-1.png 600w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/whmcs-lic-ver-1-300x183.png 300w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"></p><p>If the domain is not authorized, clicking \u201cReport it to us\u201d will take you to a screen where you can fill out a piracy report.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><div class=\"relpost-thumb-wrapper\"><div class=\"relpost-thumb-container\"><h3>Related posts:</h3><div style=\"clear: both\"></div><div style=\"clear: both\"></div><div class=\"relpost-block-container\"><a class=\"relpost-block-single\" href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/meme-monday-slightly-derailed-by-whmcs/\"><div class=\"relpost-custom-block-single\" style=\"width: 150px; height: 215px;\"><div class=\"relpost-block-single-image\" alt=\"Meme Monday: Slightly Derailed by WHMCS\" style=\"background: transparent url(https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/u